title: Currie, United earn Capitol titles
text:
COTTAGE GROVE — It was a banner day for two Jefferson County teams and one area individual as the 2015 Capitol Conference Cross Country Meet was held at McCarthy Park in Cottage Grove. 
Marshall hosted the event. 
Deerfield/Cambridge came away with the most hardware as both the United boys and girls won South Division titles. Meanwhile, D/C’s Spencer Currie was the overall South Division champion. 
Currie covered the 5k course in 16:35. Following Currie were Gus Kaiser (16:39) and Jay Nikolay (16:54) in second and fourth place, respectively. 
All three received first-team All-Capitol Conference honors. 
Deerfield/Cambridge, which had a meet-best 22 points, also took first in the final conference standings. 
The United girls dominated the South Division field with 30 points and also finished first in the final conference standings. 
Sydney Currie’s second-place time of 19:32 paved the way while following Currie across the finish line were Lilly Pollasky (20:10) and Reece Matheson (20:22) in fifth and sixth place, respectively. 
Currie, Pollasky and Matheson earned first-team All-CC honors. 
NORTH DIVISION 
Lakeside Lutheran’s Mitchel Georgi won the Capitol North Meet with a 5k time of 16:13. 
Georgi’s time led the Warriors to a runner-up finish (57 points) behind champion Poynette. Lakeside also finished second in the final conference standings. 
Georgi earned first-team All-Capitol honors, as did Elijah Tesch (7th, 16:54). Charlie Pingel (12th, 17:29) and Ben Tweit (14th, 17:33) ran their way to second-team honors. 
Georgi was named the 2015 Capitol North Runner of the Year. 
Lake Mills finished fifth with 115 points. Chase Scheel earned first-team honors after finishing second behind Georgi in 16:21. 
The Lakeside Lutheran girls finished third in the Capitol North Meet earning 58 points. 
Jennica Jensen led the Warriors’ way with a sixth-place time of 20:19, earning first-team All-CC honors. 
Meanwhile, Lydia Ulrich (8th, 20:35), Rachel Manteufel (9th, 20:44) and Kira Tweit (11th, 20:56) all ran their way to second-place honors. 
Lake Mills placed fifth with 109 points. The L-Cats’ Ella Quinn finished 13th (21:01) to earn second-team honors. 
Deerfield/Cambridge, Lakeside Lutheran and Lake Mills all will run in the Saturday’s WIAA Division 2 Pewaukee Sectional. Girls will run at 10 a.m., followed by boys at 10:45.
